dji.sdk.api.GroundStation

Class DJIGroundStationWaypoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.GroundStation.DJIGroundStationWaypoint

  • public class DJIGroundStationWaypoint
extends java.lang.Object

    DJI Ground Station waypoint

    Way point is the major element for way point task. For Inspire 1 and Phantom 3 series, some actions are allowed to be executed while the drone reaches the way point target(DJIGroundStationWayPointAction). The action includes taking photo, starting record, stopping record, aircraft yaw, gimbal yaw and gimbal pitch.
    Version:
    V2.1.0
    Author:
    DJI Software

    • Field Detail

      • altitude

        public float altitude
        The altitude of waypoint to the drone's takeoff position. the unit is meter.

      • turnMode

        public int turnMode
        The turnMode of the aircraft at the waypoint.
        1 - anti-clockwise turning; 0 - clockwise turning.

      • heading

        public short heading
        The heading parameter will determine the heading angle while the aircraft reaches the waypoint.

      • speed

        public float speed
        The speed for heading to the waypoint.

      • stayTime

        public short stayTime
        The stayTime is the maximum time the drone can stay in one waypoint to execute actions. When the execution time for actions exceeds the stayTime, it will start to move to the next waypoint.
        (Phantom 2 Vision/Phantom 2 Vision+ support only)

      • maxReachTime

        public short maxReachTime
        The maxReachTime means the maximum time which the drone could spend on the way to the waypoint. If the trip exceeds the maxReachTime, the drone will fly to the next waypoint.

      • actionTimeout

        public short actionTimeout
        Max time for executing the all actions. if timed out and action still not completed, then the aircraft will stop actions and moving to the next waypoint.
